    dc:creator "Elliott, T. L.; Barrett, R. L.; Muasya, A. M." ;
    dc:title "Schoenus cuspidatus Rottb." ;
    trt:publishedIn <http://dx.doi.org/10.1016/j.sajb.2018.11.021> ;
    trt:treatsTaxonName <http://taxon-name.plazi.org/id/Plantae/Schoenus_cuspidatus> ;
    a trt:Treatment .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.1016/j.sajb.2018.11.021>
    bibo:endPage "535" ;
    bibo:journal "South African Journal of Botany" ;
    bibo:pubDate "2019-03-31" ;
    bibo:startPage "519" ;
    bibo:volume "121" ;
    dc:creator "Elliott, T. L.; Barrett, R. L.; Muasya, A. M." ;
    dc:date "2019" ;
    dc:title "A taxonomic revision of Schoenus cuspidatus and allies (Cyperaceae, tribe Schoeneae) - Part 1 *" ;
    fabio:hasPart <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10496598>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10496600>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10496602>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10496604>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10496606> ;
    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10496598>
    dc:description "Fig. 1. Spikelet variation in the Schoenus cuspidatus and allies group found in southern Africa: A—S. cuspidatus (lanceolate spikelet), B—S. crassus (lanceolate spikelet), C—S. auritus (lanceolate spikelet), D—S. graminifolius (lanceolate spikelet), E—S. calceolus (ovate spikelet) and F—S. ligulatus (linear-lanceolate spikelet).The black scale bar next to the spikelets represents 1 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10496598/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10496600>
    dc:description "Fig.2. Examples of nutlets from 11 species of the Schoenus cuspidatus and allies group found in southern Africa:A—S.auritus; B—S.graminifolius; C—S.ligulatus; D—S.exilis; E—S.bolusii; F— S.submarginalis; G—S.crassiculmis; H—S.quartziticus; I—S.limosus; J—S.purpurascens; and K—S.calceolus (immature).The black scale bar represents 1 mm.The mature fruits of S.calceolus and S.prophyllus are unknown." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10496600/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10496602>
    dc:description "Fig.3. Examples of plants from six species of the Schoenus cuspidatus and allies group found in southern Africa,showing the corresponding inflorescences andspikelets beneath each plant: A, G and M—S.auritus; B, H and N—S.graminifolius; C, I and O—S. ligulatus; D,J, and P—S.exilis; E,K and Q—S.bolusii; and F, L and R—S.submarginalis. The black scale bar adjacent to the inflorescences in G—L represents 10 mm, while the scale bars adjacent to the spikelets in M—R represent 1 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10496602/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10496604>
    dc:description "Fig.4. Examples of plants from six species of the Schoenus cuspidatus andallies group found in southern Africa,showing the corresponding inflorescences and spikelets beneath each plant: A,G and M—S.crassiculmis; B,H and N—S.quartziticus, C,I andO—S.limosus; D,J,and P—S.purpurascens; E,K andQ—S.prophyllus; and F,L and R—S.calceolus. The black scale bar adjacent to the inflorescences in G—L represents 10 mm, while the scale bars adjacent to the spikelets in M—R represent 1 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10496604/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10496606>
    dc:description "Fig. 5. Culm base of Schoenus calceolus showing culms grouped together by a translucent leaf sheath.The black scale bar adjacent to the base of the culms represents 10 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10496606/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

